SIMPLE: consensual
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Consensual
<hw>Con*sen"su*al</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Consent</er>, <pos>v. i.</pos>, and cf. <er>Sensual</er>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Law)</fld> <def>Existing, or made, by the mutual
consent of two or more parties.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Physiol.)</fld> <def>Excited or caused by
sensation, sympathy, or reflex action, and not by conscious volition;
<as>as, <ex>consensual</ex> motions</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Consensual contract</b></col> <fld>(Law)</fld>, <cd>a
contract formed merely by consent, as a marriage contract.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Consensus</ent>⟦br⟧
